main event: A bright, intensely pulsating white to deep red and green object was observed stationary in the sky for 30 minutes.
interesting points: The object pulsated through various colors while remaining stationary.
The object was estimated to be about 1000 miles southwest of the Azores Islands.
No electronic disturbances or radar returns were reported.
The report mentions that the apparent color changes could account for the object appearing to change color.
The report concludes the sighting as 'unidentified'.
sighted object: intensely bright, pulsating white to deep red, then green, white object
location: Approximately 1000 miles WSW of Azores Islands
